You heard that right ALL YOU CAN EAT SASHIMI.
You don't have to order nigiri, eat the fish, and hid the rice under the table or in your napkin.
Here's the scoop.
It's AYCE sushi that's open only for dinner and late nights (5 PM -2 AM) for $26.95 and if your a "good looking lady" you can save a couple dollars after 11 PM.
Desserts aren't included in AYCE, that's fine with me I don't care for dessert after doing AYCE sushi unless their dessert is better than their sushi.
AYCE sushi includes AYCE sashimi on most of their nigiri items.
AYCE has a limit of 1 dozen oysters and 4 orders of uni per person, have those that don't like oysters and uni order them and you eat them.
There's a 18% gratuity on parties of 4 or more, gladly pay for it service and food was worth more.
