I had to do some research before my trip to Vegas this past weekend because my friend and I wanted to find an AYCE sashimi restaurant.
There might be a few other restaurants out there that do this, but this was the only one that I saw many comments about the AYCE sashimi.
We arrived, got our rental car, and we were off to find this restaurant.
It was a 15 minute drive from the Mandalay Bay side of the Strip.
You could do a la carte here, but why?
The reason you should come here is if you have a big appetite and you want to eat a lot of sushi/sashimi.
My friend doesn't eat rice so we ate sashimi all night.
There were many options for us to choose from and I thought for an AYCE restaurant, the quality was pretty good.
Don't expect the high end cuts of fish you find at the elite Japanese sushi bars.
Instead, expect fresh fish and a lot of it.
We didn't bother with any of the rolls.
You can read other people's reviews for that.
We also ate many of the appetizers and I think we both agreed the frallops were the tastiest of all of the appetizers.
This isn't a buffet style kind of restaurant.
You order as you go.
I think it is easiest if you belly up to the sushi bar rather than sit at a table.
Very affordable and no problems with parking.
A local couple did mention to us that this place is often crowded when they open up for dinner.
We went around 8 pm and had no problem getting seated quickly.
I will be back!

